The former president of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, PresidentÂ Goodluck Ebele Azikiwe Jonathan GCFR, GCON has taken to his Facebook handle to share some pictures of himself and his team on their visit to Mali and Ghana respectively.
Goodluck Jonathan and his team had visited Bamako, the capital and largest city of Mali in continuation of their mediation efforts. However, he and his team had to stay overnight in Mali before moving out of the country.
Earlier today, Goodluck Jonathan and his team left Mali for, Accra, the capital of Ghana, on the Atlantic coast of West Africa, where they attended the sixth Extraordinary session of ECOWAS Authority of Heads of States and Government on the political situations in Mali, Guinea and Burkina Faso.
Goodluck Jonathan shared the pictures of himself and his team during their visits to the above mentioned countries on Facebook commending the efforts of the leaders in restoring democracy in the affected countries.
In his Facebook post, Goodluck Jonathan said that he commends the efforts of the leaders of the sub-region towards restoring democracy and resolving socio-political tensions in the affected nations in their zone.
Below are the pictures of himself and his team during the visit.
While reacting to his Facebook post, many Nigerians dived into the comment section to encourage and praise him for excellence and personality.
They told him to keep up with the good work as they so much love him and his kind of man. Below are some of the thousands of positive comments on his post.



